        The eProcurement Ontology describes objects and concepts, with definitions, attributes and relationships which are present within the European public procurement domain.
        The provision of these concepts provides the basis for a common understanding of the domain for all stakeholders ensuring the quality of data exchange and transparency.</dcterms:description>
